Nigeria Football Federation (NFF) and GAC Motor signed a partnership agreement that had all the components of a ground-breaking relationship. The union confers on GAC Motor the title of Official Automobile Partner of NFF. The signing ceremony at the GAC Headquarters in Victoria Island, Lagos marked the first time Nigeria’s football governing body was having remarkable partnership with an automobile company. “We are thrilled to extend our partnerships with GAC as our exclusive automobile partner,” said NFF President, Amaju Pinnick. “This union moves us forward in our determination to become a self-funding Football Federation. We are happy to be partners with GAC because it is a fast-growing organization with a lot of qualitative and farsighted persons, just like the NFF. After our long and hard deliberations, NFF is convinced that GAC is our ideal partner, because of its long-standing history of premium partnerships and support tied to youth development in Nigeria.” Chief Diana Chen, Chairman of CIG Motors (authorized distributors of GAC Motor in Africa) said: “Football has always been a reckoning power for uniting all interests and differences of Nigerians, over time, bringing together the old and the young from all walks of life – united in the spirit of true sportsmanship that knows no tribe, gender or religion.”  It is a three –year agreement in the first instance, but Pinnick said: “It is renewable and we believe that we are in this relationship for the long haul.” Also present at the ceremony were 1st Vice President of the NFF, Barrister Seyi Akinwunmi; NFF Executive Committee members Aisha Falode and Ganiyu Majekodunmi; NFF General Secretary, Dr. Mohammed Sanusi; NFF Director of Communications, Ademola Olajire; NFF’s Head of Marketing, Alizor Chuks; former Nigeria international and personal assistant to NFF President, Nasiru Jibril and Miss Queen Otarakpo of the NFF Legal Unit.